cff-version: 1.2.0
message: |
  If you use llm-market-sim in academic work, please cite both the software
  release (this file) and the accompanying paper. Cite the paper for the
  theoretical results (intraclass correlation, critical threshold c*) and
  the software release for the simulator, mechanism implementations, ICC
  estimator, and reproducibility artifacts.
title: "llm-market-sim: A research library for simulating markets populated by LLM and zero-intelligence agents"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Dube
    given-names: Taksch
    affiliation: Kent State University
    email: tdube@dubeinternational.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/takschdube/llm-market-sim"
license: MIT
version: 0.2.0-dev
date-released: "2026-06-15"
keywords:
  - llm-agents
  - agent-based-modeling
  - market-design
  - mechanism-design
  - call-auction
  - cognitive-monoculture
  - intraclass-correlation
  - egta
abstract: |
  llm-market-sim is a Python research library for simulating markets populated
  by large-language-model agents and zero-intelligence traders. It implements
  a pluggable Mechanism abstract base class with both pairwise-midpoint and
  uniform-price call clearing rules, a multi-provider LLM client supporting
  DeepSeek, Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google, an intraclass-correlation estimator
  for the architectural-correlation parameter rho_A, and a critical-threshold
  calculator c* = 1 / sqrt(rho_A * n) derived in the accompanying paper. It is
  the simulation backbone for cognitive-monoculture research and is designed
  to integrate as a Mechanism component with broader substrates such as
  Concordia, Magentic Marketplace, and ABIDES-MARL.
preferred-citation:
